pr_review_comment_body:
If I understand this correctly you return `1` (meaning error) in case of len/size mismatch. Whereas the previous `lseek` and `read` calls set errno, this line (53) won't, so I think you need to do this:

```
if (br != len) {
    PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, 
                    "size mismatch when reading kernel memory fd");
    return 1;
}
return 0;
```

Also, since you set the exception in here, you should do the same for the 2 calls above (`lseek` and `read`) and do `PyErr_SetFromErrno(PyExc_OSError);`.
Of course the callers of this function should just return NULL.

Also, I wouldn't bother with temporary variables here. i.e. just write it as:

```js
var graphsLink = 'perf.html#/graphs?' + $httpParamSerializer({
  series: _.map(seriesList, function(series) {
    return '[' + [ series.projectName, series.signature, 1, series.frameworkId ] + ']';
  }),
  ...
```

You can make this:
```py
class Reader(metaclass=Orange.util.Registry):
```
The all reader implementations can be iterated over with:
```py
for reader in cls.registry:
    if ext in reader.ext:
        ...
```

I mean aren't we expecting multichannel image here?
```
if multichannel:
    if convert2ycbcr:
        ...
    else:
        ...
else:
```

Put the properties on separate lines like this (it's just easier to read)

```jsx
<Dropzone 
    ref={(node) => { this.dropzone = node }} 
    className='c-files-dropzone' 
    onDrop={(files) => this.onDrop(files)} 
    disableClick={true}
    activeClassName='c-files-dropzone-active'>

I feel that instead of having a special check, we should use inheritance and just override `accept` in `GangaList` to something like:
```python
def accept(self, visitor):
    visitor.nodeBegin(self)

    for (name, item) in self._schema.simpleItems():
        if name == '_list':
            visitor.componentAttribute(self, '_list', self._getdata('_list'), 1)
        elif item['visitable']:
            visitor.simpleAttribute(self, name, self._getdata(name), item['sequence'])

    for (name, item) in self._schema.componentItems():
        if item['visitable']:
            visitor.componentAttribute(self, name, self._getdata(name), item['sequence'])

    visitor.nodeEnd(self)
```
so that the `GangaList`-specific logic is contained within `GangaList`
